This paper deals with the problem of scheduling mobile agents to deliver an item in an energy-efficient manner, which involves coordination and optimization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. The problem also involves graph theory and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization objectives and trade-offs, which could place it in the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The use of velocities and paths in the problem formulation suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of the problem and the design of approximation algorithms, which could place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category.
